SB2062 POLAMD1 Mike Osburn-GRS
3/31/2026 1:42:44 pm
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
State of Oklahoma
SPEAKER:
CHAIR:
I move to amend SB2062
Of the printed Bill
Page 3 Section 1 Lines 24
Of the Engrossed Bill
Page 3, Section 1, Line 24: By deleting after the word "designated" the
word "correctional";
Page 4, Section 1, Line 1: By deleting the word "facility" and inserting
in lieu thereof, the following: "Department of Corrections reception
center";
Page 4, Section 1, Line 2: By deleting after the word "jail" the following
phrase "and initial reception processing";
Page 4, Section 1, Line 2: By inserting after the word "The" the following
language: "defendant shall schedule a day and time within five (5) days of
sentencing to be received by the Department and upon arrival, the";
Page 4, Section 1, Line 3: By deleting after the word "shall" the phrase
"receive the defendant upon arrival";
Page 4, Section 1, Lines 5-6: By deleting all language beginning with the
word "at" through the word "Corrections"; and
Page 4, Section 1, Line 9: By inserting after the period "." the following
language: The defendant shall not receive credit for serving any days
outside the county jail or outside the custody of the Department to
include time served, deferred reception credits, earned credits and
achievement credits. Due to the defendant never being in custody, the
Department shall be directed to contact the county jail if the defendant
fails to arrive at the designated reception center and shall not be
responsible for the management of locating and placing the defendant into
custody.
AMEND TITLE TO CONFORM TO AMENDMENTS
Amendment submitted by: Mike Osburn
Adopted: _____________________________
